27/05/2003
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Bulgarian Minister of Regional Development Valentin Tserovski and European Commission Director General for Enlargement Eneko Landaburu met on Monday (26 May) and discussed co-operation, structural fund aid and the progress of Bulgaria's EU accession talks.
Tserovski briefed Landaburu on reforms, regional development, the decentralisation process and absorption of structural assistance funds.
Landaburu said he expects Bulgaria to close accession talks by 2004.
In other news, Bulgarian Foreign Minister Solomon Passy launched a four-day visit to the Middle East on Monday, with stops planned in Israel and Jordan.
(Trud, Dnevnik, BTA - 27/05/03;
BTA - 26/05/03)
